## What changed

**Root cause (from eval):** `new Response(stream, { headers })` in Next.js App Router doesn't flush HTTP status/headers until the first byte of the body is written. With ClickHouse down or an empty database, the interval never enqueued anything, so the client hung forever.

**Fix — `src/app/api/live/route.ts` (one line added):**
```typescript
start(controller) {
  // Flush headers immediately on connect — SSE clients ignore ":" comments
  controller.enqueue(encoder.encode(":\n\n"));

  intervalId = setInterval(async () => { ... }, 1000);
}
```

**Test updates — `src/app/api/live/__tests__/route.test.ts`:**
- Added new test: "immediately enqueues a keep-alive SSE comment on connect before any timer fires"
- Updated 2 existing tests to consume the keep-alive chunk before asserting on `data:` lines (factual corrections — the old assertions became impossible once a chunk is always enqueued first)

